HEADWORD: Trollop
<hw>Trol"lop</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Troll</er>
to roll, to stroll; but cf. also <er>Trull</er>.]</ety> <def>A stroller;
a loiterer; esp., an idle, untidy woman; a slattern; a slut; a
whore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

